A 29-year old cleaner, Moses Elisha, who allegedly stole his employer’s jewellery worth N5 million, on Wednesday, appeared in a Magistrates’ Court in Kaduna. Elisha, who resides at Sabon Tasha Kaduna State, is charged with two counts of conspiracy and theft. The Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Chidi Leo, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Nov. 2 at No. 9, Kenya Street Barnawa, Kaduna. Leo alleged that the defendant worked for Mrs Esther Michael, the complainant as a cleaner. The prosecutor said that on Nov. 2, when the complainant went to work, the defendant conspired with one other person, who is at large, stole her gold jewellery worth N5 million. ALSO READ: Convene NEC meeting or resign, APC governors tell Oshiomhole Driver in court for allegedly punching policeman in the face Police rescue another boy kidnapped in Kano, arrest 3… 11-year-old kidnapped in Kano, sold at Onitsha for N200,000… Those who attacked traditional ruler’s palace ‘ll be… He said that the offence contravened the provisions of sections 59 and 270 of the Penal Code Laws of Kaduna State, 2017. Elisha pleaded not guilty to the charge. Magistrate Lukman Sidi admitted him to bail in the sum of N200,000 with two sureties in like sum. Sidi ordered that one of the sureties must be a relation of the defendant. He adjourned the case until December 3 for hearing. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
